dspace-development.title: Diagnose the restarting of the Symplectic Elements IIS application within the production environment

comments.body: This may well be related to why I found the TLS connectivity issues from #600 resolved without any further actions from me.

Attempting to diagnose these restarts using Event Viewer keeps triggering the crashing of the Microsoft Management Console:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/14f8617f-79c9-4da7-bc41-ab1ae61f1c29)

Please note that there is a one hour difference (ahead) in the Elements application log for https://app.zenhub.com/workspaces/rdss-workcycles-61a4f1a12a399b001730f65a/issues/pulibrary/dspace-development/601#issuecomment-1040500276

The following is the stack trace:
![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/22367da6-9bfc-4330-988c-dcfeb9fc0ea5)

Given the log time and Elements log, the following may well be related to the root cause for these seemingly random restarts:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/1c3c8b55-8dae-45b6-b7cd-32606a2ee931)

The following settings were modified for the `Application Pool`, which *should* prevent further recycling:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/6f9f5e41-831d-49cf-a005-a86320407fc9)

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/12a06ca8-4242-4e2d-8f49-446206d2c101)

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/ec0c9db1-6811-44ff-b034-79d0a37faa98)
I am attempting to trigger another rebuild of the reporting database for the reporting synchronization. Hopefully this should finish without the process being recycled.

The CSV export for the submissions yields far over 27 items (22435):

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/43fa264f-af5a-4bf4-bc18-997f1e3f1921)
No submissions are marked as `Pending compliance`, hence I will need to filter further in order to determine the subset of 27 submissions.

I believe that this is now functioning as expected:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/5b15ea00-e070-4ebf-a1f7-345f5f018795)
I will share this with the reporting users in order to confirm that this is the expected behavior, but this may well resolve both this issue and #564

Honeybadger will not give us the source of their IPs checks to add to the firewall. They will provide authentication of uptime check requests using  Honeybadger-Token header, which contains a secret token thatâ€™s sent with each request. This will need us to setup JWT. If this works I suspect other new uses will arise.
